					<h3>Finding Items</h3>

					<p>Our observations showed that people have widely different processes to go about grocery shopping. Some go into stores prepared with a list, some tend to buy impulsively, others span both behaviors. Because these habits are so personal, we stayed away micro-managing or optimizing people's shopping in a prescriptive way. Instead, we prioritized letting users find their own way around the store with some guidance, without being intrusive.</p>
				</div>

