			<section id="takeaways">
				<div class="medium-8 medium-centered columns">
				<h1>Key Takeaways</h1>
				<h4>Reach people where they are</h4>
				<p>Our prototype tried to eliminate the need to checkout by automatically charging credit cards. Some people might readily welcome changes like completely doing away with checkout, but others felt as if they were stealing things. Many iterations tried to ease people into the process – guidance to the exit, confirmation of payment and correct groceries. Reach people where they are with technology, don't coerce them into solutions. </p>

				<h4>Incorporate all stakeholders</h4>
				<p>Our prototype was a first attempt at meeting the needs of shoppers. However, interviews with store employees and managers revealed different needs – stocking inventory and preventing fraud. One story recalled how some underage teenagers scanned a sack of potatoes but then slipped through the self-checkout with a 6-pack of beer. These are critical concerns to address before understanding the value of SmartCart as a platform.</p>

